### Describe the bug

Hello,

We have been using our blazor for a long time. But still some things about performance are not agreeable.

In the below code, we have sent a JS call that changes the visibility of an element when it returns in a button click, a very small operation.

```
@page "1"
@using Microsoft.JSInterop
@inject IJSRuntime JsRuntime;

<div style="width:700px; height:700px; background-color:red">
    <button onclick="@ChangeVisbility">ChangeVisiblity</button>
    <div style="width:50px; height:50px; background-color:yellow;visibility:@visiblity;" id="YellowDiv">    </div>
</div>

@code {
    string visiblity = "visible"; 
    public async Task ChangeVisbility()
    {
        bool isVisble = await JsRuntime.InvokeAsync<bool>("CheckVisibility");
        if (isVisble)
        {
            visiblity = "hidden";
        }
        else
        {
            visiblity = "visible";
        }
    }
}
```

**Note: Here there is necessary to send a JS call and get the result to update the Visibility.** 

In this, it works very fast in locally. But it's a bit slow when hosting it in Azure or any site.

Hosted link: https://blazorpdfviewerui.azurewebsites.net/ 

As a blazor developer, we agree it takes some time due to network latency to go to JS and get the result to update the visibility on the C# side. But our customers refuse to recognize this. Because they are all desktop customers. They used fast UI. 

Can you give us any tips to increase this performance while hosting?

**Note: We are in the IST region application hosted in the US region.**


### Expected Behavior

1. When i click the button the visibility should update immediately in the hosted environment, even both client and server in different regions as like  functionality.

### Steps To Reproduce

1. Open the link https://blazorpdfviewerui.azurewebsites.net/
2. Click the ChangeVisibility button
3. You can see the delay in updating the visibility of the element. 

